text.tspan: Life expectancy at birth in 2019 in West Sussex was 82.2 years
However, the gap in healthy life expectancy is much smaller
at 69.4 years among males 70.6 years among females
This is above the national average in England
(79.6 for males and 83.1 years for females)
As a rate, all cause deaths in West Sussex (1,096.9 per 100,000)
were significantly higher than in the South East region (902.6 per 100k)
Whilst neoplasms (cancer) and cardiovascular diseases are the biggest
contributors to mortality (deaths), some conditions which have low mortality rates
(such as musculoskeletal disorders) can cause significant levels of disability.
